        <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
            <head>Biographical/Historical Information </head>
            <p> John Greenhow was born in England in 1724. He was an enterprising merchant with
                store on Duke of Gloucester St. Additionally, he owned a Schooner which carried
                goods to and from Philadelphia. He died in 1787 and is buried in the Bruton Parish
                Churchyard. </p>
        </bioghist>
